Mrs.	1
Toller,"	1
said	1
Holmes,	1
"for	1
you	1
have	1
certainly	1
cleared	1
up	1
everything	1
which	1
puzzled	1
us.	1
And	1
here	1
comes	1
the	1
country	1
surgeon	1
and	1
Mrs.	1
Rucastle,	1
so	1
I	1
think,	1
Watson,	1
that	1
we	1
had	1
best	1
escort	1
Miss	1
Hunter	1
back	1
to	1
Winchester,	1
as	1
it	1
seems	1
to	1
me	1
that	1
our	1
locus	1
standi	1
now	1
is	1
rather	1
a	1
questionable	1
one."	1
	1
And	1
thus	1
was	1
solved	1
the	1
mystery	1
of	1
the	1
sinister	1
house	1
with	1
the	1
copper	1
beeches	1
in	1
front	1
of	1
the	1
door.	1
Mr.	1
Rucastle	1
survived,	1
but	1
was	1
always	1
a	1
broken	1
man,	1
kept	1
alive	1
solely	1
through	1
the	1
care	1
of	1
his	1
devoted	1
wife.	1
They	1
still	1
live	1
with	1
their	1
old	1
servants,	1
who	1
probably	1
know	1
so	1
much	1
of	1
Rucastle's	1
past	1
life	1
that	1
he	1
finds	1
it	1
difficult	1
to	1
part	1
from	1
them.	1
Mr.	1
Fowler	1
and	1
Miss	1
Rucastle	1
were	1
married,	1
by	1
special	1
license,	1
in	1
Southampton	1
the	1
day	1
after	1
their	1
flight,	1
and	1
he	1
is	1
now	1
the	1
holder	1
of	1
a	1
government	1
appointment	1
in	1
the	1
island	1
of	1
Mauritius.	1
As	1
to	1
